250
00:29:53,972 --> 00:29:56,497
This man has nothing to do
with our story

251
00:29:56,908 --> 00:29:59,900
But he's the one who's going
to give the story a new twist

252
00:30:39,117 --> 00:30:42,280
Watch out... step on the brakes!

253
00:30:51,963 --> 00:30:55,558
You know whose blood this is?
Yes, it's Khushi's

254
00:30:56,701 --> 00:31:00,694
The blood she donated in Chamoli
has journeyed far to reach here

255
00:31:01,039 --> 00:31:02,472
For Karan

256
00:31:12,384 --> 00:31:14,978
Lali! My child!

257
00:31:18,990 --> 00:31:21,982
Lali, just don't worry

258
00:31:22,994 --> 00:31:25,986
I've told the priest to find
another suitor for you

259
00:31:26,431 --> 00:31:28,763
You're going to be married
next week

260
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:32,333
Keep quiet, Papa.
- Why, my child?

261
00:31:32,804 --> 00:31:36,001
How can you take such decisions
without even thinking?

262
00:31:37,008 --> 00:31:41,001
Do you know what I've been through?
A groom has just walked out on me

263
00:31:41,513 --> 00:31:44,004
And you're already thinking
of another marriage?

264
00:31:45,016 --> 00:31:48,179
And I want to study further.
But you...

265
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:53,384
Yes, you wanted to study further.
But I stood in your way

266
00:31:56,027 --> 00:32:01,829
Papa, may I study further?
May I complete my MSc?

267
00:32:02,234 --> 00:32:07,399
How will you study further?
I tore up your application form

268
00:32:09,107 --> 00:32:11,268
You tore up the form
of Pune University

269
00:32:11,509 --> 00:32:13,636
But I've also applied
to the Mumbai University

270
00:32:14,045 --> 00:32:17,708
They've even called me for an interview.
With your permission...

271
00:32:18,049 --> 00:32:22,042
I'll leave for further studies.
- Bombay University?

272
00:32:25,056 --> 00:32:27,718
How about my signature?

273
00:32:31,062 --> 00:32:33,656
Big deal! It's just Virbhadra Singh

274
00:32:34,065 --> 00:32:37,057
Just a fowl-scratch.
I've done it already

275
00:32:40,538 --> 00:32:42,062
Thief!

276
00:32:49,414 --> 00:32:51,405
What's happening?

277
00:32:52,584 --> 00:32:57,487
I saw hands and legs
in plaster...

278
00:32:58,089 --> 00:33:02,082
but not on a whole face!

279
00:33:02,694 --> 00:33:05,686
Moron! Wear your glasses.
That isn't my face

280
00:33:06,097 --> 00:33:07,826
It's over here

281
00:33:19,177 --> 00:33:22,613
Bastard, you're laughing at me
instead of feeling sorry?

282
00:33:23,114 --> 00:33:25,446
You said you were going to Canada

283
00:33:38,129 --> 00:33:40,120
You can't leave me
and go away anywhere

284
00:33:40,532 --> 00:33:43,626
Karan! My son!
- Greetings

285
00:33:44,135 --> 00:33:46,330
Mother Goddess!
What's happened to my son?

286
00:33:46,671 --> 00:33:48,138
Mother Goddess...

287
00:33:51,509 --> 00:33:54,501
Why're you angry? She's crying
because you've met with an accident

288
00:33:55,146 --> 00:33:57,137
This accident took place
because she cried

289
00:33:57,315 --> 00:33:59,943
She cried before I got into the car,
so the accident happened

290
00:34:00,318 --> 00:34:02,149
Thank God she didn't come
to the airport

291
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:04,413
Had she come there, maybe
the plane would've crashed

292
00:34:05,557 --> 00:34:08,651
Send me to Canada
some way or the other

293
00:34:10,428 --> 00:34:13,659
Rascal! Why're you laughing?
I haven't cracked a joke

294
00:34:14,165 --> 00:34:17,566
It is a joke indeed.
When I broke a little toe...

295
00:34:17,902 --> 00:34:23,499
I was laid up for a week. And you...
you're laid down for 2 months at least

296
00:34:24,242 --> 00:34:28,178
Forget Canada, you can't even
go to the loo for two months

297
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:31,178
Why must he shut up?
He's right

298
00:34:31,616 --> 00:34:34,176
The doctor says you need bed rest
for at least two months

299
00:34:34,586 --> 00:34:36,577
Dad, what happens of my studies?

300
00:34:36,755 --> 00:34:39,849
You so badly wanted
to go to Canada...

301
00:34:40,191 --> 00:34:42,785
that you didn't apply
to any college here

302
00:34:43,194 --> 00:34:45,526
There's just one way now

303
00:34:46,197 --> 00:34:48,859
The Vice Chancellor at Mumbai
University is a friend of mine

304
00:34:49,267 --> 00:34:53,533
If you wish, I can have a word with
him and have a seat blocked for you

305
00:34:54,205 --> 00:34:56,196
Will you go to Mumbai then?

306
00:34:56,908 --> 00:34:59,570
What difference does it make
when I can't go to Canada anyway?

307
00:35:00,211 --> 00:35:01,610
Be it Calcutta or Mumbai

308
00:36:04,275 --> 00:36:06,266
Looks like you're a huge fan
of Ricky Martin

309
00:36:08,680 --> 00:36:12,013
I follow a rule. I fit in
with whoever's a big hit

310
00:36:12,350 --> 00:36:15,285
Whether it's Ricky Martin
or a rusty tin

311
00:37:13,511 --> 00:37:17,743
Whenever I visit a temple...
I find a lot of peace of mind

312
00:37:20,351 --> 00:37:23,343
I used to visit the temple in the
village every day. I liked going there

313
00:37:26,758 --> 00:37:29,750
Look at the politician. It looks
as if he's asking God for votes

314
00:37:32,530 --> 00:37:34,521
What did you say?
- I was only kidding

315
00:39:12,964 --> 00:39:14,955
I've seen you somewhere

316
00:39:15,533 --> 00:39:18,468
No, that wasn't what
I was getting at. Please

317
00:39:19,470 --> 00:39:25,466
But it's true that boys use this
line when they want to befriend a girl

318
00:39:25,910 --> 00:39:27,901
But that wasn't I was getting at

319
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:31,742
But I'm speaking the truth.
I've seen you somewhere

320
00:39:33,651 --> 00:39:35,642
I get that feeling too

321
00:39:37,355 --> 00:39:40,222
This is the first time we've met,
but somehow I feel...

322
00:39:40,491 --> 00:39:45,827
as if I've known you for 20 years.
- True. That's how I feel too

323
00:39:56,207 --> 00:39:58,107
You do look happy

324
00:40:02,914 --> 00:40:04,245
You're here to?

325
00:40:19,530 --> 00:40:23,523
Do you have a girlfriend?
- Yes, in our college

326
00:40:23,935 --> 00:40:26,927
In our class?
- No, in the maths section

327
00:40:27,605 --> 00:40:29,869
What's her name?
- Priya

328
00:40:30,441 --> 00:40:33,535
What hankypanky have you been upto?
- I've been upto no hankypanky

329
00:40:34,545 --> 00:40:37,946
It's the same old status problem.
She's the daughter of a rich man

330
00:40:38,282 --> 00:40:43,276
And I was brought up in an orphanage.
- Why do we always have...

331
00:40:43,554 --> 00:40:46,546
this angle in every love-story?
It's very sad!

332
00:40:50,561 --> 00:40:54,224
So now?
- Somehow or the other...

333
00:40:54,565 --> 00:40:59,298
I want to reach this letter to her.
- You plan on killing us, do you?

334
00:40:59,837 --> 00:41:01,828
Madan, please.
- Give it to me

335
00:41:24,662 --> 00:41:26,994
Listen, make him see reason

336
00:41:27,865 --> 00:41:31,130
If he doesn't understand, finish him.
- Sure

337
00:41:33,671 --> 00:41:37,300
You've had it, Vicky. Did you have to
fall in love with this guy's daughter?

338
00:41:40,611 --> 00:41:43,409
Khushi, my dear. How are you?
- I'm all right

339
00:41:44,415 --> 00:41:47,213
How's your friend doing at studies?
- Very well

340
00:42:04,635 --> 00:42:06,626
What are you doing here?

341
00:42:10,641 --> 00:42:12,302
What's that in your hand?

342
00:42:17,715 --> 00:42:20,980
Yes. How did you know?
- It's all over your face

343
00:42:21,886 --> 00:42:25,822
Don't you have any manners on
how to behave with a girl in public?

344
00:42:26,324 --> 00:42:29,316
Don't you realise what people
on the streets will think?

345
00:42:30,661 --> 00:42:33,858
You dress so well but you
behave like a cheapskate?

346
00:42:36,667 --> 00:42:39,363
You're talking any nonsense.
- My mouth, my tongue...

347
00:42:39,570 --> 00:42:42,334
I will say what I want to.
- But my ears can't listen to all this

348
00:42:42,673 --> 00:42:47,201
You're hurting my feelings.
- Feelings, I see!

349
00:42:47,678 --> 00:42:50,943
You get friendly at the first meeting
and pass love-letters the next moment!

350
00:42:51,949 --> 00:42:53,940
What feelings are those?
So cheap!

351
00:42:57,021 --> 00:42:59,285
Madam, I haven't written
this love-letter to you

352
00:42:59,557 --> 00:43:02,025
My friend Vicky wrote it
for your friend Priya

353
00:43:02,693 --> 00:43:07,289
He said that she has a strict father
who won't let her take his calls...

354
00:43:07,698 --> 00:43:10,189
and asked me if I could deliver
this letter to Priya

355
00:43:10,701 --> 00:43:13,295
When I arrived here with the letter,
I found the watchman at the gate

356
00:43:13,704 --> 00:43:17,037
I was wondering what I could do
when these cars arrived

357
00:43:17,441 --> 00:43:19,705
There were these deadly thugs
with Priya's father

358
00:43:19,877 --> 00:43:22,710
I was so shocked to see them,
I didn't know what to do

359
00:43:23,047 --> 00:43:25,038
That's when I saw you
walking out with Priya

360
00:43:25,182 --> 00:43:28,709
Khushi! She's the girl I met
at the temple

361
00:43:29,053 --> 00:43:32,511
I thought my friend's work was done.
I'd send the letter to her through you

362
00:43:32,924 --> 00:43:36,917
But you, you tell me that I don't
have any sense, any manners...

363
00:43:37,128 --> 00:43:38,823
who do you think you are?

364
00:43:39,063 --> 00:43:42,055
Maybe you have a tongue.
But you also brains to think

365
00:44:05,756 --> 00:44:09,556
We've been studying in the same college
and yet we didn't know each other

366
00:44:09,760 --> 00:44:10,988
That's strange, isn't it?

367
00:44:12,096 --> 00:44:16,760
Strange also that we're here together.
- For love

368
00:44:17,234 --> 00:44:20,169
For love?
- Yes. Priya and Vicky's love

369
00:44:23,541 --> 00:44:26,942
What did you think?
- Nothing at all

370
00:44:27,578 --> 00:44:30,376
May I ask something?
Have you ever fallen in love?

371
00:44:32,783 --> 00:44:34,182
You?

372
00:44:34,986 --> 00:44:37,113
Why not?
- Why not?

373
00:44:37,788 --> 00:44:41,383
What will I say?
Why didn't you fall in love?

374
00:44:43,494 --> 00:44:46,486
I don't know.
- You don't know how to fall in love?

375
00:44:47,999 --> 00:44:49,591
So you do?

376
00:45:03,214 --> 00:45:04,806
Shall we leave, Vicky?

377
00:45:34,278 --> 00:45:37,179
What for?
- For dropping me home

378
00:45:38,349 --> 00:45:40,840
You say thanks when a stranger
drops you home

379
00:45:41,352 --> 00:45:44,651
We're not strangers anymore.
So why be so formal?

380
00:45:45,856 --> 00:45:48,848
But I've already said thanks.
What do we do?

381
00:45:50,861 --> 00:45:53,193
You must withdraw the words

382
00:46:13,884 --> 00:46:18,287
Students, the cultural programme
at the college begins very soon!

383
00:47:56,053 --> 00:47:57,987
What happened?
- It's open

384
00:47:59,390 --> 00:48:02,382
The way you reacted over such
a trivial thing, I got really scared

385
00:48:07,198 --> 00:48:10,998
This is how friends should be.
Your friend showed trust in you...

386
00:48:11,335 --> 00:48:15,328
and gave you an open personal letter.
He must have so much of faith in you

387
00:48:16,006 --> 00:48:18,167
That's not such a big thing.
You may read it, if you wish to

388
00:48:22,012 --> 00:48:24,003
Your friend gave it to you,
because he trusted you

389
00:48:24,215 --> 00:48:26,206
You gave it to me,
because you trust me

390
00:48:26,450 --> 00:48:30,614
And my friend has faith in me.
We must never betray someone's faith

391
00:48:33,290 --> 00:48:36,691
What's the big deal?
The letter says, Dear Priya...

392
00:48:37,027 --> 00:48:39,621
I can't take you
to the movies this Friday

393
00:48:39,930 --> 00:48:42,364
I've got to go to Nashik for 2 days,
so please don't be angry with me

394
00:48:42,766 --> 00:48:45,030
I don't know what I will do
without you these 2 days

395
00:48:45,502 --> 00:48:50,030
There's so much I will miss.
You, your voice, your lovely eyes...

396
00:48:50,374 --> 00:48:54,708
your cheeks, beautiful lips,
the ones I kiss...

397
00:48:55,512 --> 00:48:59,505
your lap, in which I rest my head.
I will keep saying...

398
00:49:05,556 --> 00:49:07,547
Must you read someone's letter?

399
00:49:10,861 --> 00:49:13,227
It's a love-letter!
Full of personal emotions

400
00:49:14,498 --> 00:49:17,399
You've let your friend down.
You have betrayed his trust

401
00:49:22,239 --> 00:49:23,570
You're a dirty man...

402
00:49:29,146 --> 00:49:31,614
Are you through?
May I speak now?

403
00:49:33,083 --> 00:49:38,077
Vicky hurt his thumb, not me.
It was bleeding

404
00:49:38,689 --> 00:49:41,089
Can someone write when
he has a hurt thumb?

405
00:49:42,092 --> 00:49:46,358
No? So he dictated letter to me
and I wrote it for him. Get it?

406
00:49:47,097 --> 00:49:50,089
You need more explanation?
You just need an opportunity...

407
00:49:50,367 --> 00:49:52,835
to fly off the handle
and you won't stop

408
00:49:55,506 --> 00:49:58,703
And you even say sorry.
Know what?

409
00:49:59,109 --> 00:50:02,772
Record I'm sorry on a cassette
a thousand times...

410
00:50:03,113 --> 00:50:06,105
because you use those words
often and often. Okay?

411
00:50:31,942 --> 00:50:33,933
What happened?
- The fan-belt seems to have snapped

412
00:50:34,211 --> 00:50:36,145
I had one fixed just yesterday

413
00:50:39,016 --> 00:50:41,814
What do we do now?
- We'll lock it up and walk

414
00:50:44,488 --> 00:50:46,479
The mechanic will take it away
in the morning

415
00:50:50,661 --> 00:50:54,153
Khushi, what are you thinking about?
- Nothing

416
00:50:54,565 --> 00:50:56,556
What are you thinking about?
- Nothing

417
00:50:56,900 --> 00:50:59,892
Khushi, if I ask you a question
will you answer me?

418
00:51:03,574 --> 00:51:05,565
Whom do you like most?

419
00:51:08,579 --> 00:51:12,174
The most...? My Papa
- Of course

420
00:51:12,683 --> 00:51:16,175
Everyone of us loves his Papa.
He's the one who brings us up

421
00:51:19,523 --> 00:51:22,924
Apart from Papa,
who else do you like?

422
00:51:24,194 --> 00:51:29,928
Apart from Papa... my Mummy.
- Who can forget Mummy

423
00:51:30,534 --> 00:51:33,196
Mummy is great. At her feet
lie the heavens

424
00:51:33,937 --> 00:51:39,204
Look outside the house. Whom do
you like, apart from your folks?

425
00:51:51,288 --> 00:51:53,017
Who doesn't like him?

426
00:52:00,230 --> 00:52:05,827
Look away from the film industry.
There must be someone else?

427
00:52:08,672 --> 00:52:11,903
There is...
- There is?

428
00:52:13,510 --> 00:52:15,774
Who?
- Sachin Tendulkar

429
00:52:28,258 --> 00:52:34,060
Khushi, fathers, mothers, actors
and cricketers are all so common

430
00:52:34,765 --> 00:52:41,261
Everyone likes them. But whom do you
like specially and personally?

431
00:52:48,278 --> 00:52:50,269
Khushi... wait

432
00:52:53,283 --> 00:52:56,616
What happened?
- Tell me the name

433
00:52:57,087 --> 00:53:01,023
And I'll say that I like him.
But please don't bother me like this

434
00:53:02,292 --> 00:53:04,283
So what's the name?

435
00:53:08,298 --> 00:53:09,788
Never mind

436
00:54:28,378 --> 00:54:30,710
I was supposed to come, but...

437
00:54:32,382 --> 00:54:34,179
Have you seen Karan around?

438
00:54:34,384 --> 00:54:37,046
Is it your birthday?
- No

439
00:54:37,387 --> 00:54:40,049
Something special at home?
- No. Why?

440
00:54:40,891 --> 00:54:43,155
Your new dress and the sparkle?

441
00:54:45,195 --> 00:54:48,790
Nothing of the sort. Where's Karan?
- He's there in the corridor

442
00:54:49,566 --> 00:54:51,557
He wasn't there.
That's where I came from

443
00:54:51,902 --> 00:54:54,393
Maybe, but he's in
the telephone booth

444
00:54:56,073 --> 00:54:57,563
In the telephone booth?

445
00:55:02,412 --> 00:55:04,209
Please try to understand me

446
00:55:06,083 --> 00:55:08,745
I couldn't come because my friends
asked me to stay back

447
00:55:09,419 --> 00:55:11,410
Hello... Madhu

448
00:55:13,423 --> 00:55:16,221
We have two or three days off
again next month

449
00:55:16,760 --> 00:55:18,591
Yes, I promise

450
00:55:24,935 --> 00:55:28,098
There's still a week, right?
So let me make up for it

451
00:55:42,452 --> 00:55:44,443
Were you waiting for me?

452
00:55:46,456 --> 00:55:50,449
Well? You aren't looking nice today.
- Oh yes, that's what you will say

453
00:55:50,861 --> 00:55:53,125
Oh no, you're really
looking very beautiful

454
00:55:53,530 --> 00:55:56,465
I spoke just the opposite.
- That's how you've always been

455
00:55:56,867 --> 00:55:59,267
I was only kidding.
Why're you taking it seriously?

456
00:56:01,738 --> 00:56:03,729
Khushi's looking for you

457
00:56:08,679 --> 00:56:12,137
Were you looking for me?
- Yes

458
00:56:12,549 --> 00:56:15,814
What for?
- It was something important

459
00:56:16,219 --> 00:56:18,210
But I've forgotten what it was

460
00:56:25,929 --> 00:56:28,727
Who?
- Who and who?

461
00:56:29,499 --> 00:56:31,899
On the phone.
- Madhu

462
00:56:32,502 --> 00:56:34,231
Madhu who?
- My Ma

463
00:56:34,504 --> 00:56:36,096
Ma?
- Yes

464
00:56:38,508 --> 00:56:40,908
But you were uttering her name

465
00:56:41,511 --> 00:56:44,503
That's my mother's name and
I address my mother by her name

466
00:56:52,522 --> 00:56:53,648
Yes, Ma

467
00:56:59,930 --> 00:57:01,329
Yes, Ma

468
00:57:10,941 --> 00:57:14,206
Get cracking. The show begins in
two hours. I don't have time to waste

469
00:57:17,547 --> 00:57:19,344
Remember your step?

470
00:57:21,551 --> 00:57:24,349
You always teach me the same step.
- Because that's all I know

471
00:57:24,755 --> 00:57:27,315
What? Can you show me
something else?

472
00:57:51,581 --> 00:57:54,573
For the last 10 years, I've been
in this college like a milestone

473
00:57:55,585 --> 00:58:00,921
My juniors have turned professors.
But my friends, my cronies, I...

474
00:58:01,291 --> 00:58:03,282
Enough. I get it

475
00:58:35,325 --> 00:58:36,622
Meaning?

476
00:58:38,628 --> 00:58:41,426
Meaning... she's a friend

477
00:59:49,699 --> 00:59:53,692
If not you...

478
00:59:55,438 --> 00:59:59,704
if not you...

479
01:00:07,117 --> 01:00:11,315
if not you... life's tough

480
01:00:12,455 --> 01:00:17,722
If not with you,
my love...

481
01:00:18,128 --> 01:00:22,724
I can't even die

482
01:00:43,887 --> 01:00:48,290
I get no sleep

483
01:00:49,225 --> 01:00:51,750
If not you

484
01:00:54,864 --> 01:01:02,100
If not you... life's restless

485
01:01:49,819 --> 01:01:51,810
Pining...

486
01:01:52,822 --> 01:01:54,414
overwhelms me...

487
01:01:55,492 --> 01:02:00,156
every moment, I swear

488
01:02:01,431 --> 01:02:03,422
Last night...

489
01:02:03,833 --> 01:02:06,301
in my dreams...

490
01:02:06,836 --> 01:02:11,170
I have seen you, my love

491
01:02:13,443 --> 01:02:15,377
Laughter...

492
01:02:16,346 --> 01:02:20,840
sounds like a wail
if it isn't you

493
01:02:24,854 --> 01:02:26,845
Finding...

494
01:02:27,657 --> 01:02:32,458
is like losing...
if I can't find you

495
01:03:19,476 --> 01:03:23,913
In memories, I was lost...

496
01:03:24,914 --> 01:03:29,248
all night.
I could not go to sleep

497
01:03:30,920 --> 01:03:32,911
Loneliness...

498
01:03:33,723 --> 01:03:35,714
gnaws...

499
01:03:36,359 --> 01:03:40,921
I have no one but you

500
01:03:43,333 --> 01:03:45,528
Rose-gardens...

501
01:03:46,002 --> 01:03:50,939
appear to be barren,
if not with you

502
01:03:54,611 --> 01:03:56,602
This moment...

503
01:03:57,213 --> 01:04:02,207
seems frozen,
if not with you

504
01:05:10,920 --> 01:05:12,820
Were you scared?
- No

505
01:05:18,027 --> 01:05:19,790
What's this?
- A gift

506
01:05:19,896 --> 01:05:20,590
For me?

507
01:05:27,136 --> 01:05:29,696
What's the hurry?
Open it later

508
01:05:42,051 --> 01:05:44,042
Necessary for smokers

509
01:05:45,054 --> 01:05:47,352
Where did you buy it?
- Akbarallys

510
01:05:49,058 --> 01:05:50,855
For how much?
- 5000

511
01:05:52,262 --> 01:05:53,251
5000?

512
01:05:54,397 --> 01:05:56,388
An ashtray? For 5000?

513
01:05:58,067 --> 01:06:01,400
It's no ordinary ashtray.
It's made from French crystal glass

514
01:06:01,804 --> 01:06:04,295
It's expensive because of
its intricate art-work

515
01:06:05,074 --> 01:06:07,065
It's very nice indeed

516
01:06:08,144 --> 01:06:11,602
But you could have given me
another gift instead of this

517
01:06:15,385 --> 01:06:18,081
It's such an expensive
and beautiful ashtray...

518
01:06:19,088 --> 01:06:24,082
I'd hate to drop ash in it
when I smoke

519
01:06:26,095 --> 01:06:29,087
That's exactly why I got
this ashtray

520
01:06:29,565 --> 01:06:32,557
Because whenever you drop ash,
you must remember me

521
01:06:33,102 --> 01:06:35,832
And you must feel that
you're dropping ash...

522
01:06:36,105 --> 01:06:38,096
not in the ashtray, but on me

523
01:06:39,509 --> 01:06:43,104
So you must give up smoking

524
01:06:48,284 --> 01:06:49,774
Karan quits smoking?

525
01:06:52,388 --> 01:06:55,846
Ask me for anything else, and I'll
do it. But give up smoking? No way

526
01:06:59,128 --> 01:07:00,561
If you...

527
01:07:03,399 --> 01:07:05,128
respect me...

528
01:07:08,137 --> 01:07:10,128
you will give up smoking

529
01:07:46,209 --> 01:07:47,437
Happy?

530
01:08:51,240 --> 01:08:53,037
For the exams.
I'm studying

531
01:11:13,549 --> 01:11:16,814
That's not nice.
- What?

532
01:11:17,153 --> 01:11:19,383
That which you're doing

533
01:11:21,591 --> 01:11:23,183
Reading a book is a nice thing.

534
01:11:23,392 --> 01:11:27,055
In any case, it isn't porn.
It's a college book

535
01:11:27,496 --> 01:11:29,726
I'm not talking about
what you're reading

536
01:11:30,132 --> 01:11:32,396
I'm talking about the thing
you've been staring at

537
01:11:35,605 --> 01:11:38,073
Yes, I've been taking a good look

538
01:11:38,474 --> 01:11:40,942
Don't switch the topic.
You...

539
01:11:44,847 --> 01:11:46,838
you were staring at my waist

540
01:11:48,417 --> 01:11:51,147
Don't pretend! You were watching it!
- I didn't

541
01:11:51,420 --> 01:11:53,411
You did too!
- I didn't, I say

542
01:11:53,889 --> 01:11:57,416
And I say you did. You did!
I caught you staring at it!

543
01:12:03,833 --> 01:12:08,429
Well, maybe my eyes wandered
when I was turning a page

544
01:12:09,038 --> 01:12:11,165
But I didn't have any intentions

545
01:12:11,641 --> 01:12:15,441
You haven't been here a minute,
nor have you read a page...

546
01:12:15,945 --> 01:12:18,436
but you looked at it a dozen times!
- Now look, Khushi...

547
01:12:18,848 --> 01:12:23,046
you're mistaking me.
- What...? I'm making a mistake...

548
01:12:23,319 --> 01:12:24,911
or was it you?

549
01:12:28,457 --> 01:12:31,449
Remember all those things! When
I gave you Vicky's open letter...

550
01:12:31,727 --> 01:12:34,195
when I told you about its contents,
what did you say?

551
01:12:34,463 --> 01:12:36,454
One must never look at
other's private affairs

552
01:12:36,632 --> 01:12:41,968
You called me so many names!
Didn't you?

553
01:12:42,471 --> 01:12:46,840
When I told you that he had hurt
his thumb and that I had written...

554
01:12:47,143 --> 01:12:49,270
the letter for him,
you said sorry to me

555
01:12:49,478 --> 01:12:50,877
Didn't you?

556
01:12:52,515 --> 01:12:54,380
Never mind that.
Let's talk about our first meeting

557
01:12:54,483 --> 01:12:57,213
When I gave you that letter
Vicky wanted delivered to Priya...

558
01:12:57,486 --> 01:12:59,477
what conclusion did you jump to?
That I was giving you the letter

559
01:12:59,655 --> 01:13:01,646
You yelled so much at me

560
01:13:10,499 --> 01:13:13,059
Didn't you yell at me?
But when you got to know the truth...

561
01:13:13,235 --> 01:13:17,501
you said sorry. Didn't you?
I know what you want

562
01:13:17,940 --> 01:13:20,500
You want everyone to praise your
beauty, to be crazy about you...

563
01:13:20,843 --> 01:13:23,004
and say I love you to you.
And when someone does that...

564
01:13:23,245 --> 01:13:25,110
you get worked up,
you kick up a fuss...

565
01:13:25,247 --> 01:13:29,240
you start accusing him and say that
he's after girls. Isn't that right?

566
01:13:29,685 --> 01:13:33,314
Talk about me...
not about other girls

567
01:13:33,723 --> 01:13:37,523
What do you know about
girls' psychology? What?

568
01:13:37,893 --> 01:13:40,327
We don't pretend! I don't pretend!
But you do!

569
01:13:42,531 --> 01:13:43,793
You do!

570
01:13:44,767 --> 01:13:47,258
What did you do at the restaurant
the other day?

571
01:13:47,603 --> 01:13:52,870
You deliberately dropped your spoon,
so you could use my spoon to eat!

572
01:13:53,542 --> 01:13:56,875
You did put on an act then.
What were you hiding on?

573
01:13:58,614 --> 01:14:02,141
The other day, you said your car had
broken down and that we'd have to walk

574
01:14:02,551 --> 01:14:06,544
And what did you ask me?
Whom did you like most?

575
01:14:06,956 --> 01:14:08,719
You bored me to death!

576
01:14:09,625 --> 01:14:12,560
And when your daddy come to the
college, you introduced everyone...

577
01:14:19,001 --> 01:14:21,367
Why didn't you say it freely?

578
01:14:22,571 --> 01:14:26,029
Why did you hestitate then?
What feelings were you hiding?

579
01:14:26,575 --> 01:14:29,567
Oh sure, despite
knowing everything...

580
01:14:29,912 --> 01:14:32,312
why've you been acting as
if you didn't know anything?

581
01:14:32,581 --> 01:14:34,378
What will I take that for?

582
01:14:34,650 --> 01:14:37,312
Despite knowing everything,
you gifted me an ashtray

583
01:14:37,653 --> 01:14:39,587
Okay, you gave that to me
as a friend

584
01:14:39,855 --> 01:14:42,187
But when I was talking to my Ma
the other day...

585
01:14:42,391 --> 01:14:43,915
when I was showering kisses on her...

586
01:14:44,026 --> 01:14:46,494
why did you badly
want to know the truth?

587
01:14:46,762 --> 01:14:50,323
You calmed down only after you
got to know that Madhu's my Ma

588
01:14:51,634 --> 01:14:55,161
You presented me an ashtray.
All right, maybe that's friendship

589
01:14:55,604 --> 01:15:00,303
But the restlessness you showed
when you wanted to know about my Ma...

590
01:15:00,609 --> 01:15:03,043
the streak of possessiveness you
showed, what do I take that for?

591
01:15:12,521 --> 01:15:15,615
Let's not stray from the point.
Didn't you stare at my waist?

592
01:15:17,293 --> 01:15:19,625
Haven't you loved me?

593
01:15:19,995 --> 01:15:21,986
No.
- I didn't stare either

594
01:15:28,637 --> 01:15:32,630
I happen to talk to a girl
and she finds faults with me!

595
01:15:33,642 --> 01:15:35,974
I can't ever be friends
with an egoistic girl like her!

596
01:15:36,212 --> 01:15:38,203
Even if we are friends,
it's never going to lead to love

597
01:15:38,380 --> 01:15:40,371
Even if we fall in love,
we'll never marry

598
01:15:40,516 --> 01:15:42,507
And even if we somehow
make it to the marriage altar...

599
01:15:42,651 --> 01:15:47,054
I'll say that I can't marry a girl
like her and run away from there!

600
01:15:50,659 --> 01:15:51,853
What a girl!

601
01:16:01,070 --> 01:16:05,006
You have no right to
talk about my character

602
01:16:07,042 --> 01:16:10,671
I'll forget that I ever
met someone called Karan

603
01:16:12,681 --> 01:16:16,674
You and I have nothing
to do with each other

604
01:16:57,490 --> 01:16:59,981
She looks like a twin-sister
of our master

605
01:17:01,260 --> 01:17:05,253
Excuse me, you're not
our master's twin, are you?

606
01:17:05,665 --> 01:17:08,657
Oh no. There are only
sisters in our family

607
01:17:10,002 --> 01:17:12,994
It's the master himself.
What disguise is this, Master?

608
01:17:13,339 --> 01:17:18,276
What? People go to great lengths
to have an album released

609
01:17:18,678 --> 01:17:21,272
I've only changed my name.
From Madan to Badan Bhosle

610
01:17:21,681 --> 01:17:25,549
So what's wrong?
- Name an album of yours, Master

611
01:17:26,118 --> 01:17:28,746
Don't be stubborn, my love
- How about humming the tune?

612
01:17:29,288 --> 01:17:31,813
The tune? It's fantastic

613
01:17:32,558 --> 01:17:36,289
I've really worked hard on this song.
When it's released...

614
01:17:36,629 --> 01:17:40,463
it's going to kick up a storm.
Want me to sing it for you?

615
01:17:43,302 --> 01:17:46,533
The bud of the night,
blossoms by day

616
01:17:47,039 --> 01:17:50,634
She's mischievous...
she wanders everywhere

617
01:17:51,310 --> 01:17:54,905
What else will I say?

618
01:17:55,314 --> 01:17:57,646
Don't be stubborn, my love

619
01:18:07,326 --> 01:18:10,659
That's a number from Asha Bhosle's
hit album Jaanam Samjha Karo

620
01:18:11,330 --> 01:18:14,493
What nonsense!
That's the title of a movie!

621
01:18:15,334 --> 01:18:18,132
The album of the same name was a hit,
but the film was shit

622
01:18:20,640 --> 01:18:25,009
What's between you and me?
- That's for you to decide, sir

623
01:18:25,344 --> 01:18:28,006
I'll decide later. Now tell me
what do you mean to me?

624
01:18:28,214 --> 01:18:30,205
Your secretary, sir.
- And what's a secretary's job?

625
01:18:30,349 --> 01:18:34,012
You must go out in the market and
find out which album is doing well...

626
01:18:34,253 --> 01:18:37,518
and what the get up is...
so that they don't clash with ours

627
01:18:38,357 --> 01:18:40,018
What sorry?

628
01:18:40,459 --> 01:18:44,361
Well, sir...
- No wells! That's it

629
01:18:45,631 --> 01:18:48,122
Want me to sing another song?
- Sure. Go ahead

630
01:18:49,368 --> 01:18:52,860
What would I do,
if not die?

631
01:18:53,272 --> 01:18:56,764
You're the chosen one
in thousands...

632
01:18:57,176 --> 01:18:59,041
my love

633
01:19:35,481 --> 01:19:39,417
Do not be mistaken.
I haven't come here for a compromise

634
01:19:42,655 --> 01:19:44,646
Why? Is that wrong?

635
01:19:45,057 --> 01:19:46,820
I don't want to...

636
01:19:48,694 --> 01:19:50,218
with you...

637
01:19:53,766 --> 01:19:57,429
I don't want any argument.
I have something important to say

638
01:19:58,571 --> 01:20:01,165
During the summer vacations
when we were not around...

639
01:20:01,574 --> 01:20:05,442
a lot of things have taken place.
Vicky went to meet Priya at her place

640
01:20:05,845 --> 01:20:08,177
He mistook her father for her
and awakened him

641
01:20:08,614 --> 01:20:10,241
He was caught

642
01:20:12,651 --> 01:20:15,449
Priya's father is holding her
captive in the house

643
01:20:16,455 --> 01:20:18,446
Did Vicky attend class?
- No

644
01:20:18,991 --> 01:20:23,121
The love affair we promoted
is now facing problems

645
01:20:24,597 --> 01:20:27,464
I'm talking about Vicky
and Priya's love affair

646
01:20:30,603 --> 01:20:32,161
Did you meet Priya?

647
01:20:35,007 --> 01:20:37,942
I mean, have you?
- Yes

648
01:20:38,811 --> 01:20:42,474
I've come from her house right now.
She was crying

649
01:20:43,282 --> 01:20:51,883
I told her not to worry. To unite her
with Vicky is my duty, I promised her

650
01:20:52,491 --> 01:20:56,825
And you have promised your friend
to unite the two of them

651
01:20:58,764 --> 01:21:02,495
So, to honour the promise
I've made to my friend...

652
01:21:02,902 --> 01:21:06,497
and for you to honour the promise
you've made to your friend, we must...

653
01:21:08,507 --> 01:21:09,997
We must?

654
01:21:12,511 --> 01:21:15,173
We must get together
and unite them

655
01:21:20,519 --> 01:21:26,515
We must... what I'm saying is that
...I want to make it clear

656
01:21:30,796 --> 01:21:34,527
In uniting them, the relationship
we are going to share...

657
01:21:34,934 --> 01:21:37,198
is what I'll decide right now

658
01:21:39,738 --> 01:21:45,540
It will not be love, no friendship
and no relationship at all

659
01:21:50,616 --> 01:21:54,552
Our relationship will last as long
as they are united

660
01:21:58,791 --> 01:22:03,888
I hope you will do that

661
01:22:05,998 --> 01:22:09,934
That you will do it,
I am convinced

662
01:22:12,638 --> 01:22:16,301
What can I say now?
You've said what I wanted to

663
01:22:18,577 --> 01:22:20,909
Shall we go to meet Vicky?

664
01:22:40,666 --> 01:22:43,931
You're the limit! You couldn't
wait for two months

665
01:22:47,606 --> 01:22:52,134
All I want to know is what you told
Priya's old man when you woke him up

666
01:22:52,478 --> 01:22:54,469
Priya darling, here I am?
Or was it...

667
01:22:54,613 --> 01:22:56,410
Sorry, Uncle. Wrong number?

668
01:22:59,618 --> 01:23:02,416
This is exactly why I tell you
not to fall in love!

669
01:23:02,788 --> 01:23:06,417
Look at me. I'm such a happy man!
And why?

670
01:23:06,892 --> 01:23:11,955
Because I'm not in love with someone!
And I don't have any problems like you

671
01:23:12,932 --> 01:23:16,231
Look at your face. You look like
the perfect jilted-Iover

672
01:23:24,109 --> 01:23:30,309
To hide your pain and fake a laughter
is nothing but stupidity

673
01:23:30,849 --> 01:23:33,977
What?
- I'm talking about Vicky's pain

674
01:23:34,653 --> 01:23:36,553
The one you're feeling too

675
01:23:37,656 --> 01:23:41,649
Will it solve the problem by
feeling the pain and crying? No

676
01:23:45,397 --> 01:23:48,662
Just concentrate on your studies,
Vicky. As for your love...

677
01:23:49,068 --> 01:23:52,663
leave it to us. To unite you
with Priya is our responsibility

678
01:23:55,240 --> 01:23:58,835
Can't you trust my words?
All right

679
01:23:59,678 --> 01:24:03,944
But you do trust your love,
don't you? If your love is true...

680
01:24:04,283 --> 01:24:07,480
it'll surely unite the two of you.
Am I right?

681
01:24:09,688 --> 01:24:13,283
If our love is true,
it'll surely unite us

682
01:24:18,097 --> 01:24:21,362
Yes.
- Yes, yes indeed

683
01:24:41,787 --> 01:24:44,517
Where's the need to walk?
I'll drop you home

684
01:24:48,727 --> 01:24:53,391
You needn't necessarily be my
girlfriend for me to drop you home

685
01:24:54,533 --> 01:24:57,730
It doesn't need a relationship at all.
You could say...

686
01:24:58,070 --> 01:25:00,334
you've taken a ride
in a stranger's car

687
01:25:00,806 --> 01:25:04,071
And I'll think I gave a ride
to a girl who was a stranger

688
01:25:07,146 --> 01:25:11,742
If you still want to walk,
it's upto you

689
01:25:12,751 --> 01:25:14,946
What can I do about it?

690
01:25:15,487 --> 01:25:18,149
I live in the hostel now.
Not in that flat

691
01:25:19,758 --> 01:25:23,421
To distance myself from some one,
I had to stay at the hostel

692
01:25:27,966 --> 01:25:30,230
I'll drop you at the hostel then

693
01:26:24,623 --> 01:26:30,823
Two strangers,
where are they headed?

694
01:26:31,563 --> 01:26:33,724
Where are they going?

695
01:26:39,538 --> 01:26:44,237
Angry with each other...

696
01:26:44,943 --> 01:26:49,175
they appear to be,
even as they drive on

697
01:27:00,225 --> 01:27:06,858
Two strangers...
where are they headed?

698
01:27:07,299 --> 01:27:09,460
Where are they going?

699
01:27:15,207 --> 01:27:19,871
Angry with each other...

700
01:27:20,679 --> 01:27:24,877
they appear to be,
even as they drive on

701
01:28:13,432 --> 01:28:15,263
Awake...

702
01:28:15,701 --> 01:28:17,726
asleep...

703
01:28:18,270 --> 01:28:20,261
Iost?

704
01:28:20,739 --> 01:28:22,604
Ask them

705
01:28:33,952 --> 01:28:38,514
Stop faking anger...
be friends again

706
01:28:38,957 --> 01:28:43,951
Do not break each other's hearts,
that isn't a nice thing to do

707
01:28:49,968 --> 01:28:51,959
From a distance...

708
01:28:52,237 --> 01:28:54,228
up close...

709
01:28:55,040 --> 01:28:59,636
they torment each other,
they go together

710
01:29:42,054 --> 01:29:46,388
Desire, hatred...

711
01:29:47,025 --> 01:29:51,018
what exactly do they
want in love?

712
01:30:02,240 --> 01:30:04,708
Yes and no...

713
01:30:05,177 --> 01:30:07,577
is all they say

714
01:30:07,946 --> 01:30:12,383
What's in their hearts?
No one knows

715
01:30:18,490 --> 01:30:23,052
Longing in their eyes,
to see each other...

716
01:30:24,062 --> 01:30:28,328
they're afraid,
they go together

717
01:30:39,077 --> 01:30:45,482
Two strangers...
where are they headed?

718
01:30:46,151 --> 01:30:48,415
Where are they going?

719
01:30:54,459 --> 01:30:58,759
Angry with each other...

720
01:30:59,564 --> 01:31:03,864
they appear to be,
even as they drive on

721
01:31:36,234 --> 01:31:39,465
I have't done anything this time.
It has stalled on its own

722
01:31:51,149 --> 01:31:53,140
The wire of the spark-plug
has come off

723
01:32:31,623 --> 01:32:34,456
God! I haven't seen anything
- What?

724
01:32:36,695 --> 01:32:38,185
Nothing

725
01:32:49,474 --> 01:32:53,604
When a stranger drops me home,
I always thank him

726
01:32:54,613 --> 01:32:57,207
That's a habit of mine.
- Nice habit too

727
01:33:08,426 --> 01:33:13,955
Because of my native tongue, you got
to know that I'm from the villages!

728
01:33:14,599 --> 01:33:16,226
You want to rob me?
- No, sir

729
01:33:16,301 --> 01:33:20,237
Thief! I asked you to take me
to Mumbai University and...

730
01:33:20,639 --> 01:33:22,971
you've been taking me around Mumbai!

731
01:33:23,542 --> 01:33:25,840
You've been driving
around the same place!

732
01:33:26,244 --> 01:33:28,508
Forget it, sir.
It's human to err

733
01:33:28,680 --> 01:33:31,012
Looks like you're
hand in glove with him

734
01:33:34,252 --> 01:33:36,914
Please let him go, Uncle

735
01:33:39,257 --> 01:33:41,555
Come with me.
I'll give you a ride

736
01:33:42,694 --> 01:33:46,596
You don't appear to be a cabbie.
Why will you give me a ride?

737
01:33:46,932 --> 01:33:48,923
He's the one who'll take me there.
You go on

738
01:33:51,269 --> 01:33:54,067
Until you leave, no one else
will be able to move from here

739
01:33:54,606 --> 01:33:56,733
The traffic's come to a standstill
because of you

740
01:33:58,276 --> 01:34:01,803
I study at the Bombay University too.
Come with me, I'll take you there

741
01:34:06,284 --> 01:34:08,081
You take me to be an idiot?

742
01:34:11,289 --> 01:34:13,086
The moron!

743
01:34:15,627 --> 01:34:19,290
Son, how do you live in this city?

744
01:34:20,732 --> 01:34:23,633
Everyone here appears to be
a fraud to me

745
01:34:25,303 --> 01:34:27,203
But you're a nice boy

746
01:34:28,640 --> 01:34:30,972
Guess what I like most about you?

747
01:34:33,645 --> 01:34:35,306
Your smile

748
01:34:37,315 --> 01:34:40,978
Do you know my daughter?
- Who?

749
01:34:46,324 --> 01:34:49,725
How would you know her? There must
be so many girls in the college

750
01:34:51,329 --> 01:34:56,733
There's this hostel near the college.
- Which hostel?

751
01:34:57,502 --> 01:35:02,337
Now what is the name?
Mary...

752
01:35:07,579 --> 01:35:10,343
Right, St Mary's Girls Hostel!

753
01:35:12,350 --> 01:35:15,080
Do you know where the hostel is?
- Know?

754
01:35:17,589 --> 01:35:20,581
I can't ever forget that hostel.
- Why?

755
01:35:21,760 --> 01:35:24,160
There's this girl I know
who stays there

756
01:35:24,729 --> 01:35:28,722
She's no ordinary girl, mind you.
She has a massive ego

757
01:35:29,434 --> 01:35:31,698
What?
- Ego

758
01:35:32,771 --> 01:35:36,366
Meaning?
- Ego meaning...

759
01:35:38,043 --> 01:35:40,876
she thinks she's the last word

760
01:35:44,382 --> 01:35:48,842
Even when she knows she's wrong,
she'll never say sorry

761
01:35:52,891 --> 01:35:54,882
This damn ego...

762
01:35:55,894 --> 01:36:01,389
how will I explain it?
This girl...

763
01:36:02,133 --> 01:36:05,569
she's stubborn, a bit eccentric...

764
01:36:09,407 --> 01:36:14,811
I get it. That daughter
of an ass is arrogant

765
01:36:15,413 --> 01:36:16,812
Yes, arrogant!

766
01:36:21,419 --> 01:36:26,413
I wanted to tell you about the girl,
but you've spoken about her family!

767
01:36:34,699 --> 01:36:41,434
She's just a girl, you know.
If she can be so arrogant...

768
01:36:41,840 --> 01:36:44,434
am I any less?
- Oh yes

769
01:36:49,180 --> 01:36:50,442
Oh yes!

770
01:36:52,917 --> 01:36:53,906
Oh yes!

771
01:36:58,456 --> 01:37:03,052
That's the block.
- Thank you very much

772
01:37:03,795 --> 01:37:09,631
I live in Chamoli, son. If you ever
visit the place, do meet me

773
01:37:11,469 --> 01:37:12,697
See you

774
01:37:15,206 --> 01:37:17,003
Lali! My child!

775
01:37:19,544 --> 01:37:21,478
How are you?
- I'm fine

776
01:37:21,946 --> 01:37:24,471
Why're you so late?
- What will I tell you?

777
01:37:25,016 --> 01:37:27,814
On my way, I got into
a fight with a cabbie

778
01:37:28,286 --> 01:37:31,983
It was a terrible fight and
this nice boy really helped me

779
01:37:32,824 --> 01:37:35,292
He... one moment!

780
01:37:37,228 --> 01:37:39,492
Hello son... hello!

781
01:37:39,898 --> 01:37:41,763
Come here

782
01:37:43,201 --> 01:37:44,691
Lali, come here

783
01:38:01,519 --> 01:38:05,512
As I was telling you, I got into
a fight with a crazy cabbie

784
01:38:06,124 --> 01:38:09,252
And a decent boy came along
and helped me. He's the one

785
01:38:10,061 --> 01:38:11,858
This is my daughter, Lali

786
01:38:25,543 --> 01:38:28,808
Have some coffee before you leave.
- Thanks, but I've got to go

787
01:38:29,247 --> 01:38:33,240
Oh no. Back in the village, we don't
let a guest go away without...

788
01:38:33,551 --> 01:38:36,816
extending our hospitality. If you
leave without having coffee...

789
01:38:37,055 --> 01:38:39,888
I'm going to feel bad.
Tell him to stay, dear

790
01:38:43,761 --> 01:38:45,752
Please have some coffee

791
01:38:48,566 --> 01:38:53,970
I'll go and lock my car.
- All right. Let's go

792
01:38:56,774 --> 01:38:59,334
I don't want to get married.
- Why not?

793
01:38:59,978 --> 01:39:02,572
When you wanted to study further,
I agreed with you

794
01:39:02,914 --> 01:39:05,906
And now that I want you to get
married, you must listen to me

795
01:39:07,585 --> 01:39:09,849
Come, son.
Have some coffee

796
01:39:10,388 --> 01:39:12,982
I just don't agree!
- Why not?

797
01:39:13,391 --> 01:39:15,791
Look at her, son.
She's not listening to me

798
01:39:21,399 --> 01:39:24,926
You must listen to Papa, mustn't you?
- Do you know what he's saying?

799
01:39:25,603 --> 01:39:28,595
And this is between the two of us.
You aren't interfering

800
01:39:29,073 --> 01:39:32,270
You'll get a slap, Lali.
He's a guest...

801
01:39:32,610 --> 01:39:37,104
is that how you talk to a guest?
What wrong have I said, son?

802
01:39:37,615 --> 01:39:40,345
I'm looking for a groom for her
and she's refusing me

803
01:39:44,889 --> 01:39:50,350
When a girl keeps refusing to get
married, what does it mean?

804
01:39:50,995 --> 01:39:54,624
It means there is someone else
she loves

805
01:39:55,700 --> 01:39:59,966
I'm not against that. All I want
is for you to have a nice wedding

806
01:40:00,705 --> 01:40:06,439
But how should the suitor be?
He must be just like this boy

807
01:40:08,646 --> 01:40:13,447
Clean-hearted, innocent eyes...
a handsome young man

808
01:40:15,987 --> 01:40:19,980
If there is someone you love,
tell me about it

809
01:40:22,660 --> 01:40:24,924
I'm not in love with anyone

810
01:40:25,663 --> 01:40:29,064
If you really don't love anyone,
you must obey your Papa

811
01:40:31,669 --> 01:40:35,662
Papa, I'm willing to get married.
- Wow!

812
01:40:37,775 --> 01:40:39,470
This is amazing!

813
01:40:39,677 --> 01:40:42,407
I've been trying for so long
and she just wouldn't agree

814
01:40:42,680 --> 01:40:46,013
You spoke to her just once
and viola! She agreed!

815
01:40:46,851 --> 01:40:49,684
Looks like we share the
same birth-sign, son

816
01:40:50,688 --> 01:40:53,680
I had a problem with the cabbie
and you solved

817
01:40:54,692 --> 01:40:57,684
And this problem of her marriage
you have solved too

818
01:40:58,696 --> 01:41:02,928
I'm happy to have achieved
what I set out to do

819
01:41:03,468 --> 01:41:06,869
Lali, I'm leaving by this
evening's train

820
01:41:07,305 --> 01:41:09,239
Do look after yourself, okay?

821
01:41:09,574 --> 01:41:12,509
Come on... drop me on the way

822
01:41:16,814 --> 01:41:20,716
Lali, I forgot to tell you
something very important

823
01:41:21,719 --> 01:41:24,449
There's a girl he knows
who stays here

824
01:41:26,257 --> 01:41:29,192
They have a fight going
between themselves

825
01:41:31,729 --> 01:41:34,391
Never mind, Uncle. Please...
- Now wait a moment

826
01:41:34,732 --> 01:41:37,530
Won't I do anything for all the help
you've extended to me?

827
01:41:37,902 --> 01:41:39,460
What will people say?

828
01:41:39,737 --> 01:41:46,734
She's a very arrogant girl, Lali.
As he said, she's very stubborn too

829
01:41:47,178 --> 01:41:50,170
Not just stubborn, she's...

830
01:41:51,749 --> 01:41:56,083
a bit mental, eko...
what word did you use?

831
01:41:56,754 --> 01:42:01,191
Never mind, Uncle. Forget it...
- Give me the word! What was it?

832
01:42:04,962 --> 01:42:10,161
Yes! Ego!
She's possessed by ego!

833
01:42:10,768 --> 01:42:14,363
Like spirits taking possession
of people's bodies...

834
01:42:14,772 --> 01:42:17,468
this girl is possessed with ego!

835
01:42:19,243 --> 01:42:23,771
Ask the girl not to
fight with him, dear

836
01:42:24,182 --> 01:42:28,175
He's a very nice boy. Even my Papa
believes he's a very nice boy

837
01:42:28,686 --> 01:42:30,677
Bring the two of them together.
Okay?

838
01:42:33,057 --> 01:42:37,187
Will that be enough or do you want me
to stay over for your help, son?

839
01:42:37,595 --> 01:42:39,790
No thank you, Uncle.
You've done so much!

840
01:42:40,198 --> 01:42:42,792
That's all right...
See you

841
01:42:43,334 --> 01:42:48,397
She's a fool to get into a fight
with a nice boy like you

842
01:42:48,973 --> 01:42:52,136
